f the European Parliament]] (2014\u2013present)]]\n{|class=wikitable\n|-\n!Election year\n!No. of<br>overall votes\n!% of<br>overall vote\n!No. of<br>overall seats won\n!+/\u2013\n|-\n![[1979 European Parliament election in West Germany|1979]]\n|1,662,621\n|5.9 (4th)\n|{{composition bar|4|81|hex={{Free Democratic Party (Germany)/meta/color}}}}\n|{{increase}} 4\n|-\n![[1984 European Parliament election in West Germany|1984]]\n|1,192,624\n|4.8 (5th)\n|{{composition bar|0|81|hex={{Free Democratic Party (Germany)/meta/color}}}}\n|{{decrease}} 4\n|-\n![[1989 European Parliament election in West Germany|1989]]\n|1,576,715\n|5.6 (6th)\n|{{composition bar|4|81|hex={{Free Democratic Party (Germany)/meta/color}}}}\n|{{increase}} 4\n|-\n![[1994 European Parliament election in Germany|1994]]\n|1,442,857\n|4.1 (6th)\n|{{composition bar|0|99|hex={{Free Democratic Party (Germany)/meta/color}}}}\n|{{decrease}} 4\n|-\n![[1999 European Parliament election in Germany|1999]]\n|820,371\n|3.0 (6th)\n|{{composition bar|0|99|hex={{Free Democratic Party (Germany)/meta/color}}}}\n|{{steady}} 0\n|-\n![[2004 European Parliament election in Germany|2004]]\n|1,565,431\n|6.1 (6th)\n|{{composition bar|7|99|hex={{Free Democratic Party (Germany)/meta/color}}}}\n|{{increase}} 7\n|-\n![[2009 European Parliament election in Germany|2009]]\n|2,888,084\n|11.0 (4th)\n|{{composition bar|12|99|hex={{Free Democratic Party (Germany)/meta/color}}}}\n|{{increase}} 5\n|-\n!'''[[2014 European Parliament election in Germany|2014]]\n|986,253\n|3.3 (7th)\n|{{composition bar|3|96|hex={{Free Democratic Party (Germany)/meta/color}}}}\n|{{decrease}} 9\n|-\n!'''[[2019 European Parliament election in Germany|2019]]\n|2,028,353\n|5.4 (7th)\n|{{composition bar|5|96|hex={{Free Democratic Party (Germany)/meta/color}}}}\n|{{increase}} 2\n|}\n\n=== State Parliaments ===\n[[File:Bundesarchiv B 145 Bild-F052013-0020, Kiel, FDP-Bundesparteitag, Klumpp.jpg|thumb|[[Werner Klumpp]], interim Minister-President of the Saarland from 26 June 1979 to 5 July 1979]]\n[[File:Reinhold Maier.jpg|thumb|[[Reinhold Maier]], first and only Minister-President of [[W\u00fcrttemberg-Baden]] (1946\u20131952) and first Minister-President of Baden-W\u00fcrttemberg (1952\u20131953)]]\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!rowspan=2|State Parliament\n!rowspan=2|Election year\n!rowspan=2|No. of<br>overall votes\n!rowspan=2|% of<br>overall vote\n!colspan=3|Seats\n!rowspan=2|Government\n|-\n!No.\n!\u00b1\n!Position\n|-\n![[Landtag of Baden-W\u00fcrttemberg|Baden-W\u00fcrttemberg]]\n|[[2016 Baden-W\u00fcrttemberg state election|2016]]\n|445,430\n|8.3 (5th) {{increase}}\n|{{composition bar|12|143|hex={{Free Democratic Party (Germany)/meta/color}}}}\n|{{increase}} 5\n|{{decrease}} 5th\n|{{no|Opposition}}\n|-\n![[Landtag of Bavaria|Bavaria]]\n|[[2018 Bavarian state election|2018]]\n|687,842\n|5.1 (6th) {{increase}}\n|{{composition bar|11|205|hex={{Free Democratic Party (Germany)/meta/color}}}}\n|{{increase}} 11\n|{{decrease}} 6th\n|{{no|Opposition}}\n|-\n![[Abgeordnetenhaus of Berlin|Berlin]]\n|[[2016 Berlin state election|2016]]\n|109,431\n|6.7 (6th) {{increase}}\n|{{composition bar|12|160|hex={{Free Democratic Party (Germany)/meta/color}}}}\n|{{increase}} 12 \n|{{increase}} 6th\n|{{no|Opposition}}\n|-\n![[Landtag of Brandenburg|Brandenburg]]\n|[[2019 Brandenburg state election|2019]]\n|51,660\n|4.1 (7th) {{increase}}\n|{{composition bar|0|88|hex={{Free Democratic Party (Germany)/meta/color}}}}\n|{{steady}} 0\n|{{steady}} 7th\n|{{eliminated|Extra-parliamentary}}\n|-\n![[B\u00fcrgerschaft of Bremen|Bremen]]\n|[[2019 Bremen state election|2019]]\n|87,107\n|6.0 (6th) {{decrease}}\n|{{composition bar|5|84|hex={{Free Democratic Party (Germany)/meta/color}}}}\n|{{decrease}} 1\n|{{decrease}} 6th\n|{{no|Opposition}}\n|-\n![[Hamburg Parliament|Hamburg]]\n|[[2020 Hamburg state election|2020]]\n|199,263\n|4.9 (6th) {{decrease}}\n|{{composition bar|1|121|hex={{Free Democratic Party (Germany)/meta/color}}}}\n|{{decrease}} 8\n|{{decrease}} 6th\n|{{no|Opposition}}\n|-\n![[Landtag of Hesse|Hesse]]\n|[[2018 Hesse state election|2018]]\n|215,946\t\n|7.5 (5th) {{increase}}\n|{{composition bar|11|137|hex={{Free Democratic Party (Germany)/meta/color}}}}\n|{{increase}} 5\n|{{steady}} 5th\n|{{no|Opposition}}\n|-\n![[Landtag of Lower Saxony|Lower Saxony]]\n|[[2017 Lower Saxony state election|2017]]\n|287,957\n|7.5 (4th) {{decrease}}\n|{{composition bar|11|137|hex={{Free Democratic Party (Germany)/meta/color}}}}\n|{{decrease}} 3\n|{{steady}} 4th\n|{{no|Opposition}}\n|-\n![[Landtag of Mecklenburg-Vorpommern|Mecklenburg-Vorpommern]]\n|[[2016 Mecklenburg-Vorpommern state election|2016]]\n|24,475\n|3.0 (6th) {{increase}}\n|{{composition bar|0|71|hex={{Free Democratic Party (Germany)/meta/color}}}}\n|{{steady}} 0\n|{{steady}} 6th\n|{{eliminated|Extra-parliamentary}}\n|-\n![[Landtag of North Rhine-Westphalia|North Rhine-Westphalia]]\n|[[2017 North Rhine-Westphalia state election|2017]]\n|1,065,307\n|12.6 (3rd) {{increase}}\n|{{composition bar|28|199|hex={{Free Democratic Party (Germany)/meta/color}}}}\n|{{increase}} 6\n|{{increase}} 3rd\n|{{yes|CDU\u2013FDP}}\n|-\n![[Landtag of Rhineland-Palatinate|Rhineland-Palatinate]]\n|[[2016 Rhineland-Palatinate state election|2016]]\n|132,262\n|6.2 (4th) {{increase}}\n|{{composition bar|7|101|hex={{Free Democratic Party (Germany)/meta/color}}}}\n|{{increase}} 7\n|{{steady}} 4th\n|{{yes|SPD\u2013FDP\u2013Greens}}\n|-\n![[Landtag of the Saarland|Saarland]]\n|[[2017 Saarland state election|2017]]\n|17,419\n|3.3 (6th) {{increase}}\n|{{composition bar|0|51|hex={{Free Democratic Party (Germany)/meta/color}}}}\n|{{steady}} 0\n|{{steady}} 7th\n|{{eliminated|Extra-parliamentary}}\n|-\n![[Landtag of the Free State of Saxony|Saxony]]\n|[[2019 Saxony state election|2019]]\n|97,438\n|4.5 (6th) {{increase}}\n|{{composition bar|0|119|hex={{Free Democratic Party (Germany)/meta/color}}}}\n|{{steady}} 0\n|{{increase}} 6th\n|{{eliminated|Extra-parliamentary}}\n|-\n![[Landtag of Saxony-Anhalt|Saxony-Anhalt]]\n|[[2016 Saxony-Anhalt state election|2016]]\n|54,525\n|4.9 (6th) {{increase}}\n|{{composition bar|0|87|hex={{Free Democratic Party (Germany)/meta/color}}}}\n|{{steady}} 0\n|{{steady}} 6th\n|{{eliminated|Extra-parliamentary}}\n|-\n![[Landtag of Schleswig-Holstein|Schleswig-Holstein]]\n|[[2017 Schleswig-Holstein state election|2017]]\n|105,770 \n|11.5 (4th) {{increase}}\n|{{composition bar|9|73|hex={{Free Democratic Party (Germany)/meta/color}}}}\n|{{increase}} 3\n|{{steady}} 4th\n|{{yes|CDU\u2013Greens\u2013FDP}}\n|-\n![[Landtag of Thuringia|Thuringia]]\n|[[2019 Thuringian state election|2019]]\n|55,422\n|5.0 (6th) {{increase}}\n|{{composition bar|5|90|hex={{Free Democratic Party (Germany)/meta/color}}}}\n|{{increase}} 5\n|{{increase}} 6th\n|{{no|Opposition}}\n|}\n\n== Leadership ==\n[[File:Hans-Dietrich Genscher Dezember 2007 CJD Koenigswinter 2.jpg|thumb|upright|[[Hans-Dietrich Genscher]] served almost continuously as Foreign Minister and Vice Chancellor from 1974 to 1992]]\n[[File:Wolle-bundestag.jpg|thumb|upright|[[Wolfgang Gerhardt]]]]\n\n=== Party chairmen ===\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!colspan=2|Leader\n!From\n!To\n|-\n!style=\"background:{{Free Democratic Party (Germany)/meta/color}};\" |1\n|style=\"width:200px;\"|[[Theodor Heuss]]\n|style=\"width:125px;\"|1948\n|style=\"width:125px;\"|1949\n|-\n!style=\"background:{{Free Democratic Party (Germany)/meta/color}};\" |2\n|[[Franz Bl\u00fccher]]\n|1949\n|7 March 1954\n|-\n!style=\"background:{{Free Democratic Party (Germany)/meta/color}};\"|3\n|[[Thomas Dehler]]\n|7 March 1954\n|24 January 1957\n|-\n!style=\"background:{{Free Democratic Party (Germany)/meta/color}};\"|4\n|[[Reinhold Maier]]\n|24 January 1957\n|29 January 1960\n|-\n!style=\"background:{{Free Democratic Party (Germany)/meta/color}};\"|5\n|[[Erich Mende]]\n|29 January 1960\n|29 January 1968\n|-\n!style=\"background:{{Free Democratic Party (Germany)/meta/color}};\"|6\n|[[Walter Scheel]]\n|29 January 1968\n|1 October 1974\n|-\n!style